ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course was challenging but I learned a great deal - I would certainly recommend this class to other students.
This class is essential. I appreciate that I had a chance to take it my first semester here.

I would recommend this class to another graduate student. I know that it influenced how I approach study design especially, but also had broader implications for issues such as ethics and validity of research in our field.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned invaluable information about research methods that I will be able to use in graduate school and beyond.

I cannot imagine doing research or a dissertation without an understanding of research methods. I came to graduate school with some knowledge, but this class expanded it tremendously and has been already very helpful.

I know that this course influenced how I approached designing the study I am working on this year and how I conceptualized its methodology. I know that the issues discussed in the class will continue to be relevant for my future research.
